  12 Mar 2008; Gilles Dartiguelongue <eva@gentoo.org> -cheese-2.21.5.ebuild,
  +cheese-2.22.0.ebuild:
  bump to 2.22, imported ebuild from sunrise
   * drop gnome-vfs, replaced by gio
   * drop libglade to use gtkbuilder

  16 Jan 2008; Alexandre Rostovtsev (tetromino) <tetromino@gmail.com>
  -cheese-0.3.0.ebuild, +cheese-2.21.5.ebuild:
  Version bump. Cheese is now an official part of Gnome.

  27 Dec 2007; Alexandre Rostovtsev (tetromino) <tetromino@gmail.com>
  -cheese-0.2.4.ebuild, +cheese-0.3.0.ebuild:
  Version bump. Add USE flag for v4l (needed for old webcams). Drop the
  linguas hack, since cheese now uses standard Gnome build system.

  28 Nov 2007; Stefan Schweizer <genstef@gentoo.org> cheese-0.2.4.ebuild:
  works without gstreamer v4l for me - only v4l2 is enough

